formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
> As per the information and explanation given and records & documents provided to me by the partners of the firm, the partnership firm has borrowed monies from various persons for development of the projects of the firm. Unsecured loans have not been borrowed for any specific project and it is a general loan for all the projects and hence it is not possible for me to bifurcate these borrowed amount to a specific project and hence the amount of loans shown here above are the total borrowings for all the projects of the partnership firm. The partnership firm does not have any outstanding loan from Banks or Financial Institutions for development of the above mentioned project.					
> The amount shown in point no. 1 (i) (d) as Amounts payable to State Government or competent authority or any other statutory authority of the State or Central Government towards stamp duty, transfer charges, registration fees etc. of Rs. 69,79,823/- for registration fees and stamp duty paid has to be change due to some erroneous entry was made in unaudited books of accounts while issuing Form-3 at time of RERA registration process. Hence after verification of accounts it has been came to notice that one entry for stamp duty for an amount of Rs. 6,62,000/- made wrongly which was paid for acquiring some another land and hence proportionate amount of Phase-1 has to be reduced at Rs. 66,99,891/-.					
> The partnership firm has not made any agreement to sale in case of bookings of any plot and directly sale deed has been executed at the time of sale.					
> 70% of total amount received in RERA Collection Bank Account i.e. 11,55,89,390/- should have been deposited in RERA Retention Bank Account, out of that the amount of Rs. 5,11,64,400/- has not been deposited into RERA Retention Bank Account. As per information provided to me by partners of the firm RERA Collection Bank Account is automatically operated by Bank System. Further Rs. 21,67,000/- received in respect of plot no. 30 directly deposited in Current Bank Account of Partnership firm and has not been deposited in RERA Collection Bank Account and hence 70% of same has also not been deposited to RERA Retention Bank Account. Amount Withdrawn till date at point no. 7 includes the 70% of the amount received in RERA Collection Bank Account or Current Bank Account which have not deposited in RERA Retention Bank Account.
